[Tables listing recent isolates of the 26 known BTV serotypes are available at http://www.reoviridae.org/dsRNA_virus_proteins/ReoID/BTV-isolates.htm. The collection of the 26 serotypes at Pirbright is available at http://www.reoviridae.org/dsRNA_virus_proteins/ReoID/BTV-Nos.htm#BTV-26.

Results of further investigations addressing the goat-related strain described above, and particularly its potential infectivity and pathogenicity in ruminants are anticipated with interest.

Traditionally, Corsica shares its BTV serotypes with neighbouring Sardinia. It will be interesting to note if the described (new?) virus is detected there as well. - Mod.AS

Maps of France can be seen at http://www.trussel.com/maig/image/frdeptb.jpg and https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=2540317,35433. - Sr.Tech.Ed.MJ]
